Their differences underscore a series of domestic dramas, culminating in a nervous breakdown that sends Mabel to a psychiatric hospital for six months, only to return to a home environment on even thinner ice than before. The improvisational style central to Cassavetes' vision is at its most acute throughout A Woman Under the Influence. Like its title heroine, the film threatens to veer out of control at any time, its shape and scope defined not by narrative but by the emotional upheaval at its center. Embracing the full spectrum of the Longhettis' relationship, from seismic bursts of high drama to small, even trivial moments of domestic tedium, its long scenes relentlessly probe every nook and cranny of the family's life, drawing out each moment for maximum emotional impact; the film is by turns beautiful and ugly, illuminating and frustrating, and it features a performance by Rowlands as heartwrenching and unforgettable as any ever committed to celluloid.~ Jason Ankeny, All Movie Guide

Author: Agatha Christie

Daughter of Fortune.label: Daughter of Fortune
Daughter of Fortune.description: Daughter of Fortune is a novel by Isabel Allende, and was chosen as an Oprah's Book Club selection in February 2000. Wikipedia
Author: Isabel Allende

De nakomer.label: De nakomer
De nakomer.description: De nakomer is a novel by Dutch author Maarten 't Hart. It was first published in 1996. Wikipedia
Author: Maarten 't Hart

Daughters of the Moon.label: Daughters of the Moon
Daughters of the Moon.description: Daughters of the Moon is a novel series by Lynne Ewing. It is about four fictional girls, later five, who are mortal goddesses and fight an ancient evil called The Atrox. They each have different powers, destinies, and dark sides. Wikipedia
Author: Lynne Ewing
Books: Daughters of the Moon - The Final Eclipse
Daughters of the Moon - The Becoming
Daughters of the Moon - The Lost One
Daughters of the Moon - The ChoiceMore

De re metallica.label: De Re Metallica
De re metallica.description: De re metallica is a book cataloguing the state of the art of mining, refining, and smelting metals, published a year posthumously in 1556 due to a delay in preparing woodcuts for the text. Wikipedia
Author: Georgius Agricola

Dead Souls.label: Dead Souls
Dead Souls.description: Dead Souls is a novel by Nikolai Gogol, first published in 1842, and widely regarded as an exemplar of 19th-century Russian literature. The purpose of the novel was to demonstrate the flaws and faults of the Russian mentality and character. Wikipedia
Author: Nikolai Gogol

Dialectic of Enlightenment.label: Dialectic of Enlightenment
Dialectic of Enlightenment.description: Dialectic of Enlightenment is a work of philosophy and social criticism written by Frankfurt School philosophers Max Horkheimer and Theodor W. Adorno and first published in 1944. Wikipedia
Dialectic of Enlightenment.type: Book by Theodor W. Adorno and Max Horkheimer

Dexter in the Dark.label: Dexter in the Dark
Dexter in the Dark.description: Dexter in the Dark is a 2007 novel written by Jeff Lindsay. This is the third book in the Dexter series, preceded by the 2004 novel Darkly Dreaming Dexter—which formed the basis of the Showtime television ... Wikipedia
Author: Jeff Lindsay

Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Sh.label: Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships
Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Sh.description: The Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships is the official reference work for the basic facts about ships used by the United States Navy. Wikipedia

Dictionary of the Khazars.label: Dictionary of the Khazars
Dictionary of the Khazars.description: Dictionary of the Khazars A Lexicon Novel is the first novel by Serbian writer Milorad Pavic, published in 1984. Originally written in Serbian, the novel has been translated into many languages. Wikipedia
Author: Milorad Pavic´

Different Seasons.label: Different Seasons
Different Seasons.description: Different Seasons is a collection of four Stephen King novellas with a more serious dramatic bent than the horror fiction for which King is famous. The four novellas are tied together via subtitles that relate to each of the four seasons. Wikipedia
Author: Stephen King

Die Feuerzangenbowle.label: Die Feuerzangenbowle
Die Feuerzangenbowle.description: Die Feuerzangenbowle is a 1944 German film, directed by Helmut Weiss and is based on the book of the same name. It follows the book closely as its author, Heinrich Spoerl, also wrote the script for the movie. Wikipedia

Digital Fortress.label: Digital Fortress
Digital Fortress.description: Digital Fortress is a techno-thriller novel written by American author Dan Brown and published in 1998 by St. Martin's Press. Wikipedia
Author: Dan Brown

Disgrace (novel).label: Disgrace
Disgrace (novel).description: Disgrace is a novel by J. M. Coetzee, published in 1999. It won the Booker Prize. The writer was also awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature four years after its publication. Wikipedia
Author: J. M. Coetzee

Doctor Sax.label: Doctor Sax
Doctor Sax.description: Doctor Sax is a novel by Jack Kerouac published in 1959. Kerouac wrote it in 1952 while living with William S. Burroughs in Mexico City. Wikipedia
Author: Jack Kerouac

Dodsworth.label: Dodsworth
Dodsworth.description: Dodsworth is a 1936 American drama film directed by William Wyler. Sidney Howard based the screenplay on his 1934 stage adaptation of the 1929 novel of the same name by Sinclair Lewis. Wikipedia

Dubliners.label: Dubliners
Dubliners.description: Dubliners is a collection of 15 short stories by James Joyce, first published in 1914. They form a naturalistic depiction of Irish middle class life in and around Dublin in the early years of the 20th century. Wikipedia
Author: James Joyce
Followed by: A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man

Dred: A Tale of the Great Dismal Swamp.label: Dred A Tale of the Great Dismal Swamp
Dred: A Tale of the Great Dismal Swamp.description: Dred A Tale of the Great Dismal Swamp is the second popular novel from American author Harriet Beecher Stowe. It was first published in two volumes by Phillips, Sampson and Company in 1856. Wikipedia
Author: Harriet Beecher Stowe

Dragonflight.label: Dragonflight
Dragonflight.description: Dragonflight is a fantasy novel by the American-Irish author Anne McCaffrey. It is the first book in the Dragonriders of Pern series. Dragonflight was first published by Ballantine Books in July 1968. Wikipedia
Author: Anne McCaffrey

Dune: House Harkonnen.label: Dune House Harkonnen
Dune: House Harkonnen.description: Dune House Harkonnen is a 2000 science fiction novel by Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson, set in the fictional Dune universe created by Frank Herbert. Wikipedia
Dune: House Harkonnen.type: Book by Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson

Dune: The Butlerian Jihad.label: Dune The Butlerian Jihad
Dune: The Butlerian Jihad.description: Dune The Butlerian Jihad is a 2002 science fiction novel by Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson, set in the fictional Dune universe created by Frank Herbert. Wikipedia
Dune: The Butlerian Jihad.type: Book by Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson

Eine Billion Dollar.label: Eine Billion Dollar
Eine Billion Dollar.description: Eine Billion Dollar is a 2001 novel by German writer Andreas Eschbach. Its plot revolves around a young pizza driver from New York City, who inherits a trillion US dollars from one of his ancestors who lived in 16th century Florence. Wikipedia
Author: Andreas Eschbach

Eleven Minutes.label: Eleven Minutes
Eleven Minutes.description: Eleven Minutes is a 2003 novel by Brazilian novelist Paulo Coelho based on the experiences of a young Brazilian prostitute called Maria, whose first innocent brushes with love leave her heartbroken. Wikipedia
Author: Paulo Coelho

Eagle Strike.label: Eagle Strike
Eagle Strike.description: Eagle Strike is the fourth book in the Alex Rider series written by British author Anthony Horowitz. The book was released in the United Kingdom on September 4, 2003 and in the United States on April 12, 2004. Wikipedia
Author: Anthony Horowitz

Engines of Creation.label: Engines of Creation
Engines of Creation.description: Engines of Creation The Coming Era of Nanotechnology is a 1986 molecular nanotechnology book written by K. Eric Drexler with a foreword by Marvin Minsky. An updated version was released in 2007. Wikipedia
Author: K. Eric Drexler

Ender's Shadow.label: Ender's Shadow
Ender's Shadow.description: Ender's Shadow is a parallel science fiction novel by the American author Orson Scott Card, taking place at the same time as the novel Ender's Game and depicting some of the same events from the point ... Wikipedia
Author: Orson Scott Card

Excession.label: Excession
Excession.description: Excession, first published in 1996, is Scottish writer Iain M. Banks's fourth science fiction novel to feature the Culture. Wikipedia
Author: Iain Banks

English As She Is Spoke.label: English As She Is Spoke
English As She Is Spoke.description: English as She Is Spoke is the common name of a 19th-century book written by Pedro Carolino, and falsely additionally credited to José da Fonseca, which was intended as a Portuguese-English conversational ... Wikipedia

Exodus (novel).label: Exodus
Exodus (novel).description: Exodus by American novelist Leon Uris is about the founding of the State of Israel. Published in 1958, it is based on the name of the 1947 immigration ship Exodus. Wikipedia
Author: Leon Uris

Expedition to Earth.label: Expedition to Earth
Expedition to Earth.description:
Expedition to Earth is a collection of science fiction short stories by Arthur C. Clarke.
There are at least two variants of this book's table of contents—in different editions of the book. Wikipedia
Author: Arthur C. Clarke

Family Without a Name.label: Family Without a Name
Family Without a Name.description: Family Without a Name is an 1889 adventure novel by Jules Verne about the life of a family in Lower Canada during the Lower Canada Rebellion of 1837 and 1838 that sought an independent and democratic republic for Lower Canada. Wikipedia
Author: Jules Verne
Followed by: The Purchase of the North Pole

Fanny Hill.label: Fanny Hill
Fanny Hill.description: Memoirs of a Woman of Pleasure is an erotic novel by English novelist John Cleland first published in London in 1748. Wikipedia
Author: John Cleland
